1. Moje *priznanje* je bilo iskreno. (My confession was sincere.)
2. Njegovo *priznanje* je izazvalo iznenađenje među prisutnima. (His admission caused surprise among those present.)
3. Ona je čekala *priznanje* svog doprinosa projektu. (She was waiting for recognition of her contribution to the project.)
4. Ulice su bile pune ljudi koji su slavili *priznanje* njihove zemlje. (The streets were full of people celebrating their country's recognition.)
5. *Priznanje* je ključno za izgradnju poverenja u odnosima. (Acknowledgment is essential for building trust in relationships.)
6. Iako je želeo da izbegne kaznu, on nije dao *priznanje* svom krivičnom delu. (Although he wanted to avoid punishment, he did not confess to his crime.)
7. Njena *priznanja* su dovela do hapšenja više osoba. (Her confessions led to the arrest of several people.)
8. Nakon dugogodišnjeg rada, dobio je zasluženo *priznanje* za svoj doprinos nauci. (After years of work, he received well-deserved recognition for his contribution to science.)
9. Očekivali su *priznanje* za svoj rad, ali su bili razočarani kada nisu dobili ništa. (They expected recognition for their work, but were disappointed when they received nothing.)
10. Njegovo *priznanje* je bilo ključno u rešavanju slučaja. (His admission was crucial in solving the case.)